 with \varphi  surjective. Then by the characterization of limits in
  Set, K\times _G H has underlying set those
  (k, h) such that \varphi (k) = \psi (h); for any h\in  H, by
  surjectivity of \varphi  there is a k\in  K so that (k, h)\in  K\times _G   H, completing the proof.

